==English==
===Etymology===
{{wikipedia}}
Named for [[w:John Hancock|John Hancock]], the first person to sign the [[w:United States Declaration of Independence]].  According to legend, he signed his name largely and clearly to be sure [[w:King George III|King George III]] could read it, causing his name to become an eponym for "signature". However, other examples show that Hancock always wrote his signature this way.

